cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using user reviews to improve software requirements elicitation. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses using machine learning techniques to classify information contained in user reviews. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper explores how user reviews can provide valuable insights into user needs and preferences. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper discusses using natural language processing techniques to analyze user reviews. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the potential impact of user reviews on product development and user satisfaction.
